<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pyongyang Rallies Back Student Protests in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pyongyang Rallies Back Student Protests in South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0804053494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0520 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804053494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- Students of Kim Il-song 
University and Pyongyang University of Agriculture held rallies 
and voiced support to the struggle of the South Korean students 
and people for checking rice market opening by the authorities. 
  Speakers at the rallies noted that, with the market of farm 
and livestock products including the rice market sold off to the 
United States by the South Korean Kim Yong-sam group, South 
Korean agriculture is facing a total bankruptcy, the 6 million 
peasants will lose the means of livelihood soon and its 
catastrophic effect will sweep the economy as a whole. 
  Referring to the staunch struggle of the students belonging 
to the South Korean Federation of General Student Councils 
(Hanchongnyon), the peasants and other people of South Korea 
against rice market opening by the Kim Yong-sam group, they said 
this was an explosion of anger and grievances against those who 
seek to prolong their despicable power by selling the people's 
right to existence and a righteous patriotic action to defend 
the dignity and interests of the nation. 
  They said the treacherous Kim Yong-sam puppet regime must be 
overthrown and an independent democratic government be 
established, if rice market opening is to be checked in South 
Korea and the dignity and interests of the nation be defended. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

