<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   King Sihanouk Arrives in Phnom Penh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Sihanouk Arrives in Phnom Penh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0804052594 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0400 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0804052594 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 8 Apr (AKP) -- Accompanied by his wife, 
Queen Monineat Sihanouk, His Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk 
arrived in Phnom Penh today, 8 April, from the DPRK. 
  Norodom Sihanouk, reenthroned as king of Cambodia last 
September, has since been hospitalized in Beijing for cancer 
treatment. He travelled to Pyongyang early this month before 
returning to Cambodia. 
  According to a schedule arranged by the Royal Palace 
cabinet, 
the king will preside over a people's audience on 12 April to 
solve five urgent problems from among the grievances aired by 
the Cambodian people as selected by his high privy councillors. 
  A roundtable meeting between government leaders and the head 
of the Khmer Rouge faction under the king's lofty chairmanship 
has also been arranged. 
  Last month, government forces took control of several Khmer 
Rouge-held bases, including Anlung Veng and Pailin, in the 
region bordering Thailand. King Sihanouk launched an appeal 
from Beijing calling on the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] 
and the Khmer Rouge faction to put a halt to their fighting. 
  Samdech Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen, 
respectively first and second prime ministers, have declared 
that the RGC has adopted an "open-door" policy toward the Khmer 
Rouge, allowing them a chance to reintegrate themselves into the 
national community. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

