<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thai King, Queen Make Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Thai King, Queen Make Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrive in Vientiane </H4>

<F P=102> BK0804105494 Vientiane KPL in English 0909 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0804105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Vientiane, April 8 (KPL) -- His Majesty King 
Phumiphon Adunyadet of Thailand and Her Majesty Queen Sirikit, 
arrived here today for an official visit to Lao PDR [Lao 
People's Democratic Republic] at the invitation of Lao President 
Nouhak Phoumsavan. 
  An official ceremony to welcome their majesties the king and 
queen of Thailand with their party including Her Royal Highness 
Princess Sirinthon took place at the National Assembly. 
  This morning the king and the queen attended a ceremony of 
presenting the friendship bridge across the Mekong River. The 
handover ceremony was performed by Australian Prime Minister 
Paul Keating, who paid an official visit to Laos on April 5-6. 
This was part of the first ever visit to Laos by the King of 
Thailand. [passage omitted on biography of Thai king] 

</TEXT>

