<H3> <TI>   U.S. Air Crashes in Okinawa Trigger Protests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Air Crashes in Okinawa Trigger Protests </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Governor Makes Statement </H4>

<F P=102> OW0704143794 Naha OKINAWA TIMES in Japanese 7 Apr 94 Morning 
Edition p 1--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0704143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha OKINAWA TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of Okinawan Governor Masahide Ota's statement on 6 </F>
April the crash of a USMC helicopter at Futenma Air Station] 
  [Text] The statement of Governor Masahide Ota is as 
follows: 
  I have not yet fully been informed of the details of the 
accident, but I am greatly frustrated with repeated accidents by 
U.S. Forces. My impression is that the increase in accidents is 
part of a sequence caused by U.S. defense budget cuts. If so, I 
cannot help feeling great fear about the recurrence of such 
accidents. The U.S. Forces say their training must continue to 
fulfill their duties defined in the Japan-U.S. Security Treaty. 
I am wondering if we cannot be free from the danger and 
problems until the security treaty is scrapped. 

</TEXT>

