<H3> <TI>   Deputy Governor on Helicopter Crash </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Governor on Helicopter Crash </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804210594 Naha RYUKYU SHIMPO in Japanese 7 Apr 94 Evening 
Edition p 1--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0804210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha RYUKYU SHIMPO </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An H-46 helicopter crashed at the Futenma Air 
Station on 6 April. In reaction, Mitsuki Tomon, lieutenant 
governor of the Okinawa Prefectural Government, called on 
Donald. R Gardner, commander of U.S. Forces on Okinawa, at Camp 
Zukeran on the morning of 7 April to deliver to the commander a 
letter demanding a thorough investigation into the cause of the 
crash and the prevention of a recurrence. The helicopter 
crashed after an F-15 fighter crashed while taking off from 
Kadena Air Base on 4 April. Therefore, she strongly protested to 
the commander about the helicopter crash. She also protested to 
the U.S. Consulate General in Okinawa. 
  On the afternoon of 7 April, Shigeru Akamine, deputy chief 
of 
the Okinawa Prefectural Government Public Affairs Office, will 
protest to the Naha Defense Facilities Administration Bureau 
about the helicopter crash. 

</TEXT>

