<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Source on DPRK Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Source on DPRK Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0904043194 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 6 Apr 94 
Evening Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0904043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Japanese Government source said on 6 April: 
"North Korea is not expected to arm itself with nuclear 
weapons, but in framing Japanese defense policy, the government 
must take into account the possibility that Pyongyang could arm 
itself with nuclear weapons." 
  His comments came in response to North Korea's suspected 
nuclear weapons development, an issue that heightened tensions 
on the Korean peninsula after Pyongyang refused to allow 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) inspectors to check 
nuclear sites. 
  His remarks indicated that the government should take into 
account the situation in North Korea in its continuing review of 
the Guidelines for Defense Build-Up. 
  On the need to defuse tensions on the Korean peninsula, the 
government source stressed the need to think of ways which would 
lead North Korea to act moderately. 
  He said: "North Korea is currently in a state of starvation 
and Chinese food aid is needed." 

</TEXT>

