<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDPJ Proposes Coalition Nuclear Issue Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPJ Proposes Coalition Nuclear Issue Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0904063894 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 7 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0904063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The "Foreign Policy Forum" headed by House of 
Representatives member Hajime Ishii, a ruling coalition policy 
study panel, held its second round of meetings in the Diet on 6 
April. Issei Inoue, vice chairman of the ruling Social 
Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], briefed the forum on the 
results of his recent visit to China and the situation in North 
Korea. 
  During the meeting, Mr. Inoue said: "In an effort to resolve 
the issue of North Korea's suspected nuclear development, I 
propose sending a delegation composed of legislators from the 
ruling coalition parties to the United States, China, North and 
South Korea. I also want to work for the stability of Northeast 
Asia by arranging a meeting between President Clinton and North 
Korean President Kim Il-song." 
  It was decided at the meeting that senior legislators of the 
ruling coalition parties would discuss the proposal. 

</TEXT>

