<H3> <TI>   SDF Expects Passage of Rescue Operations Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDF Expects Passage of Rescue Operations Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0904131994 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 8 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0904131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a regular news conference on 7 April, Tetsuya 
Nishimoto, Joint Staff Council Chairman of the Self-Defense 
Forces [SDF], touched on the issue of North Korea's suspected 
development of nuclear weapons. Asked about rescuing Japanese 
staying in South Korea if the situation on the Korean peninsula 
should become tense, he said: "Our operation should not deviate 
from the law. Japanese staying there will feel relieved when a 
bill on revising the SDF Law submitted to the Diet passes 
through the Diet. I hope the bill will be adopted as early as 
possible." In this way, he expressed hopes that the bill on 
revising the SDF Law which allows the SDF to use 
government-owned planes for rescue operations will be enacted at 
an early date. 

</TEXT>

