<H3> <TI>   Government Rejects Corruption Allegations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Rejects Corruption Allegations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804141894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1303 GMT 8 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0804141894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 8 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The press 
office of the Mongolian Government has released officially 
regarding the public accusations addressing a number of high 
ranking officials including the prime minister, as involved in 
the abuse of official position and bribery. [sentence as 
received] The statement said that the Prime Minister P. Jasray 
considers such allegations as being designed to undermine the 
prestige of and confidence in the government and applied to the 
court in this reference. P. Jasray emphasized that as notes the 
governmental press office, the government would be steadily 
struggle with any cases of abuse of official position and 
bribery. [sentence as received] Availing this opportunity the 
press office stated also that the prime minister is not going to 
take part in the today's meeting, announced by the Mongolian 
Democratic Association, as was informed earlier by a member of 
the Great State Hural T. Elbegdorj which was not agreed upon 
with himself. 

</TEXT>

