<H3> <TI>   Journalists Propose Changing Media Status </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Journalists Propose Changing Media Status </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0804143394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1310 GMT 8 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0804143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 8 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Association of Free Journalists of Mongolia (AFJM) has put 
forward a proposal to change the current status and jurisdiction 
of the national radio and television. The association is 
considering that it is necessary to reorganize the radio and 
television functioning currently as the state mass media means 
and create on their basis parallel operating stations. In 
reference to the character and property ownership there should 
be functioning state, public and private radio and television 
stations, the association notes. 
  The availability of powerful mass media means belonging to 
the government makes it impossible to develop free journalistic 
notes the statement. 

</TEXT>

