<H3> <TI>   Electricity Shortages in Capital To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electricity Shortages in Capital To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0704174594 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1345 GMT 7 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0704174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 7 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The proper 
functioning of power supply enterprises of the Mongolian capital 
is not to be improved greatly shortly as soon as Russia started 
two days ago supplying electricity which was ceased by the 
beginning of the current year due to the delay in payments on 
the part of Mongolia. But as is cleared up now, the failures in 
power supply were and are stipulated by more serious reasons 
connected with a poor organization of labour, irresponsibility 
and loosening discipline of those dealing with as well as other 
shortcomings in the work of the coal mining enterprises. 
According to the Mongolian television, at the major heat and 
power stations of the city there is the coal stock left only for 
a few days so they are trying to make use of them as much longer 
as possible which means that the current practice of cutting of 
the power supply for several times a day would be continued for 
a uncertain period up to a normalizing of the coal mining. 

</TEXT>

