<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S.-ROK `Air War Exercise' on 7 Apr Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S.-ROK `Air War Exercise' on 7 Apr Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0904053594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0417 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0904053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Formations of fighter 
bombers, assault planes, observation planes, reconnaissance 
planes and electronic warfare helicopters of the U.S. Air Force 
stationed in South Korea and the South Korean puppet air force 
Thursday staged an air war exercise against the North in the sky 
above Yoju, Tanyang and Oeyon Islet of South Korea with the 
support of a refuelling tanker to test the capacity of 
successive strikes at long-range targets, military sources said. 
  Meanwhile, a tank group of the puppet army deployed in Paju 
County, Kyonggi Province, fired scores of shells into the 
opposite side of River Yimjin and the area of Hapo-ri and puppet 
army soldiers who took position near the demilitarized zone in 
Yinje County, South Korean Kangwon Province, blindly fired 
hundreds of large-calibre machine gun bullets. 

</TEXT>

