<F P=103> BK0804125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi is to supply 100 tons of heavy water for a 
nuclear power plant in South Korea. Under an agreement signed 
in Seoul today, the heavy water subject to international atomic 
energy safeguards will be shipped in 1997-98. The deal worth 
$23 million is the first major commercial export of heavy water 
from India which is its leading producer in the world. 

</TEXT>

