<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   AFP Reports Two Britons, Australian Abducted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AFP Reports Two Britons, Australian Abducted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1204083294 Hong Kong AFP in English 0825 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1204083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Phnom Penh, April 12 (AFP) -- Unidentified gunmen 
abducted two Britons and an Australian travelling in a taxi from 
Phnom Penh to the port town of Sihanoukville, British embassy 
officials said Tuesday. 
  "The car was stopped around 5.30 p.m. by armed gunmen, they 
were taken out of the car and ordered into the bush," an embassy 
official said. 
  The taxi driver was then ordered to drive on, he said. 
  The three, who were only identified as a male and female 
from 
Britain and a woman from Australia, were abducted near Sre Ambel 
about 130 kilometers (75 miles) south of the capital, the 
official said. 
  The embassy official refused to call the incident a 
kidnapping. 
  "No ransom has been demanded and there is no reason to 
believe one will be," he said. 
  A local police officer told AFP by telephone that he 
believed 
the Khmer Rouge were responsible. 
  "If it was government soldiers they would just ask for money 
or cigarettes," the officer said. 
  The embassy official said two of the three abducted were 
residents here and one was a tourist. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

