<H3> <TI>   Admiral Winyan Appointed Deputy Navy Commander </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Admiral Winyan Appointed Deputy Navy Commander </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1004131994 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 9 Apr 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> BK1004131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok BANGKOK POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty the King has appointed Admiral Winyan 
Santiwisat to replace Admiral Santiphap Muming as Deputy Royal 
Thai Navy Commander in Chief, the Prime Minister's Office 
announced yesterday. 
  The Royal appointment, which was made on April 2 and 
countersigned by Prime Minister Chuan Likphai, is retroactive to 
March 1, when Adm. Santiphap died of liver cancer and heart 
failure, the office said. 
  Before the appointment, Admiral Winyan was Admiral of the 
Fleet under the Navy Commander in Chief, which post will be 
taken over by Admiral Chalin Sakhonsin. 

</TEXT>

