<H3> <TI>   Vietnam Airlines Reopens Hanoi-Na San Air Route </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnam Airlines Reopens Hanoi-Na San Air Route </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1104070994 Hanoi VNA in English 0643 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1104070994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi [words indistinct] Another domestic air route, 
Hanoi-Na San (Son La Province) was reopened yesterday. This is 
the 20th air route of the national flag carrier Vietnam 
Airlines. To reopen (?the Hanoi)-Na San air service, Vietnam 
Airlines invested more than one million VND [Vietnamese dong] in 
building a new terminal and installing a new communication 
system. Together with the reoperation 10 days ago on the air 
service between Hanoi and Dien Bien Phu (Lai Chau Province) the 
Hanoi-Na San air route will meet the (?growing demands) for fast 
transport to serve tourism and business, thus helping develop 
socioeconomic activities in northern province. 

