<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Loan Projects Create 335,000 Jobs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Loan Projects Create 335,000 Jobs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1004084594 Hanoi VNA in English 0715 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1004084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 10 -- Nearly 8,000 projects 
throughout the country have got loans of about VND [Vietnamese 
dong] 420 billion from the national fund since the launching of 
a credit programme two years ago, it was reported by the Central 
State Treasury. As a result, the programme has helped create 
335,000 jobs nationwide. Leading the programme was Ho Chi Minh 
City which gave loans of VND 36.13 billion to 317 projects, 
creating 16,500 jobs. Next was Hanoi which lent VND 24.29 
billion to 229 projects attracting 19,622 workers. 
  These projects are usually small and operate in the fields 
of 
aquaculture, sea fishing, small industries and handicrafts, 
building materials production and animal breeding. The state 
treasury and the concerned branches and services are seeking 
measures to streamline lending procedures to provide credits in 
time and help to use them effectively. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

