  [Text] Tokyo, April 8 KYODO -- Liberal Democratic Party 
(LDP) Secretary General Yoshiro Mori said Friday [8 April] the 
party has no plan to appoint former Foreign Minister Michio 
Watanabe as its vice president. 
  Mori told a press conference that he has no intention of 
asking Watanabe to become LDP vice president to meet calls for 
