<H3> <TI>   ROK Students' Protest of Market Opening Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Students' Protest of Market Opening Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204042294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0414 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204042294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Eruption of Resentment" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
comments on the vigorous fighting of South Korean students and 
people against rice market opening by the Kim Yong-sam traitor 
clique which is warming up along with their anti-U.S., anti-war 
and anti-nuke struggle. Assessing this as an eruption of their 
pent-up grudge and resentment against the Kim Yong-sam group 
which has bartered away their vital rights to outside forces, 
after selling the dignity and sovereignty of the nation, the 
news analyst says: 
  The traitor Kim Yong-sam during his U.S. trip last November 
begged for an "international cooperation system" to hurt fellow 
countrymen and, in return for that, secretly promised a total 
opening of South Korea's rice market to the United States. This 
folly could be committed only by such heinous traitor as Kim 
Yong-sam who schemes to maintain and prolong his power with the 
backing of his master even if the lifeline of the six million 
farmers of South Korea must be cut off, the economy as a whole 
be driven into a fatal crisis and the entire nation fall a 
victim to a nuclear war of outside forces. 
  In an attempt to lull the angry public sentiments, the 
traitor staged the drama of dismissing the puppet minister of 
agriculture, forestry and fisheries. Behind the scene, he 
worked out a criminal document to widen the scope of farm market 
opening and is making haste with its "National Assembly 
approval." 
  With no bayonet-brandishing and deception can the fascist 
group block the righteous action of the South Korean people to 
defend the dignity of the nation and their vital rights. 
  Inevitable is the miserable doom of the treacherous regime 
of 
Kim Yong-sam. 

</TEXT>

