<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of 10-Point Reunification Plan Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of 10-Point Reunification Plan Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Signature Campaigns Reported </H4>

<F P=102> SK0804115694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1009 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- Signature campaigns 
supporting "10-point programme of the great unity of the whole 
nation for the reunification of the country" were conducted in 
Lebanon and Mozambique. 
  The signature paper was signed by the chairman of the 
Lebanese Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification and 
secretary general of the Central Committee of the Lebanese 
Federation of Workers Unions on behalf of the committee and 
federation, the chairman of the Lebanese Socialist Progressive 
Party on behalf of the 50,000 party members, the general 
secretary of the Supreme Council of the Nationalist Socialist 
Party of Syria in Lebanon on behalf of 80,000 party members and 
the chairman and the general secretary of the Lebanon-Korea 
Friendship Association on behalf of the association. 
  The signature paper was also signed by the international 
secretary of the Central Committee of the workers organisations 
of Mozambique on behalf of its 600,000 members and by the 
secretary of the Maputo committee of the Mozambique Liberation 
Front Party on behalf of the 1,500,000 citizens. 
  A signature campaign is going on in Madagascar. 
  Taking part in it are the party of the congress for the 
independence, the Monima socialist organisation, the equality 
militant, the socialist progressive party and the solidarity 
committee of Madagascar and public organisations under the 
Malagasy vanguard of revolution. 
  Some 2,300,000 people had signed the signature paper in the 
country by April 1. 
  Meanwhile, the organizing committee of the signature 
campaign 
supporting "10-point programme of the great unity of the whole 
nation for the reunification of the country" was inaugurated in 
Togo on March 30. 
  The general secretary of the Togolese people's rally, 
authorized by President Gnassingbe Eyadema, signed the signature 
paper on March 31. 

</TEXT>

