<HT>    "dreas070_c_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-070 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of 10-Point Reunification Plan Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of 10-Point Reunification Plan Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Joint Meeting Held </H4>

<F P=102> SK1104114294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1124 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1104114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- A joint meeting of the 
Government of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, 
political parties and public organisations for accelerating the 
independent and peaceful reunification of the country by 
thoroughly implementing "10-point programme of the great unity 
of the whole nation for the reunification of the country" put 
forward by the great leader President Kim Il-song took place at 
the People's Palace of Culture on Monday. 
  Attending the meeting were Kang Song-san, Politburo member 
of 
the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and premier 
of the Administration Council, Kim Pyong-sik, vice-president of 
the DPRK and chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean 
Social Democratic Party, and other representatives of political 
parties and public organisations and officials concerned. 
  Yang Hyong-sop, alternate Politburo member of the WPK 
Central 
Committee and chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly, 
delivered a report at the meeting. 
  The reporter said the 10-point programme of the great unity 
of the whole nation which was authored by the great leader and 
adopted as a joint action programme of the nation for peaceful 
reunification, for the unshakable independent and patriotic 
stand and fair and aboveboard stand running through all its 
points, serves as the most reasonable and feasible grand 
political programme of national unity and a grand charter of 
national reunification, which is acceptable to all who truly 
love the country and the nation and want the reunification of 
the country. 
  All Koreans should, above all, get united as one nation, 
irrespective of differences in ideology, idea and social system 
and occupation, in order to accomplish the historic cause of 
national reunification, the reporter said. 
  Stressing the need to arrange an arena of nationwide 
dialogue 
where the will and demand of the 70 million fellow countrymen 
could be brought together to closely unite all the Korean 
nationals in the North, the South and overseas in hearty 
response to the 10-point programme of the great unity of the 
whole nation, the reporter said: 
  All the Koreans, conscious of their heavy national 
responsibility and obligation to shape the destiny of the nation 
by themselves, must confirm through open-hearted dialogue that 
they are fellow countrymen who cannot live separated from each 
other and seek a detailed way of achieving national unity, 
transcending the ideology and system as the same nation. 
  Out of this desire, we courteously propose to the South 
Korean authorities, political parties, organizations and 
individual figures and overseas compatriots to have a national 
conference for seeking a way for great unity of the whole nation 
in Pyongyang or Seoul on the occasion of August 15 this year, a 
year before the 50th anniversary of national liberation. 
  It may be a round-table conference to be participated in by 
the authorities and representatives of political parties and 
social organizations and individuals of the North and the South 
and representatives of overseas compatriots on an equal footing. 
  The participants may have an open-hearted discussion of 
practical measures for achieving a great unity of the whole 
nation, common tasks of the nation arising as prerequisites to 
realising national reunification in the '90s and other matters 
of concern for the whole nation. 
  I consider it necessary for the successful convocation of 
the 
national conference to form a preparatory committee of the 
national conference with five representatives each from the 
North, South and overseas. 
  We think that it is desirable to have the first meeting of 
the preparatory committee in Pyongyang or Seoul in mid- May. 
  We, availing ourselves of this opportunity, hold that the 
South Korean authorities must discontinue the nuclear war 
exercises and stop seeking an "international cooperation system" 
for the great unity of the whole nation, proceeding from the 
independent stand of the nation, to create a climate favourable 
to the convocation of the national conference. 
  Speeches were made at the joint meeting by Director Chong 
Mun-san of the Secretariat of the Administration Council; 
Vice-Chairman of the C.C. [Central Committee], the Korean Social 
Democratic Party Kim Yong-ho; Director of the Secretariat of the 
C.C., the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the 
Fatherland Yu Ho-chun; and Chairman of the C.C., the League of 
Socialist Working Youth of Korea Choe Yong-hae. 
  They urged the South Korean authorities to give up their 
foolish intention to solve something by relying on outside 
forces and respond to the proposal for the convocation of the 
historical national conference, accepting the 10-point programme 
of the great unity of the whole nation. 
  A letter to the South Korean authorities, political parties, 
organizations and individual figures and compatriots overseas 
was adopted at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

