<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of 10-Point Reunification Plan Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of 10-Point Reunification Plan Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Officials Attend Meeting </H4>

<F P=102> SK1204051394 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1100 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1204051394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1100 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A joint meeting of the DPRK Government, political 
parties, and public organizations for accelerating the 
independent and peaceful reunification of the country by 
thoroughly implementing the 10-point program of the great unity 
of the whole nation for national reunification was held at the 
People's Palace of Culture on the afternoon of 11 April. 
  Placed to the front of the meeting locale was a portrait of 
the great leader of our party and our people Comrade Kim 
Il-song. Slogans read "Long live the great leader Comrade Kim 
Il-song," and "Long live the glorious Workers Party of Korea 
[WPK]." There were also slogans reading "Let all the fellow 
countrymen be united under the banner of great national unity in 
order to reunify the country," and "Let us add luster to the 
year of 1994 as a year of great national unity." 
  Attending the joint meeting were functionaries of the party, 
power organs, public organizations, religious organizations, and 
central organizations. Appearing on the rostrum were Comrade 
Kang Song-san, member of the WPK Central Committee Political 
Bureau and premier of the State Administration Council; Kim 
Pyong-sik, vice president of the DPRK and chairman of the 
Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party; Comrade 
Yang Hyong-sop, alternate member of the WPK Central Committee 
Political Bureau and chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly 
[SPA]; Comrade Kim Yong-sun, secretary of the WPK Central 
Committee and chairman of the Reunification Policy Committee of 
the SPA; Comrade Chang Chol, vice premier of the State 
Administration Council; Yu Mi-yong, chairman of the Central 
Committee of the Chondoist Chongu Party, and responsible 
functionaries of public organizations. 
  SPA Chairman Yang Hyong-sop first made a report at the joint 
meeting. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

