<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Birthday Observances Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Birthday Observances Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Commemorative Stamps Issued </H4>

<F P=102> SK0904103494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1019 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0904103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of Posts 
and Communications has brought out new memorial stamps, 
postcards and envelopes on the threshold of the 15th of April. 
  Printed on stamps are Mt. Paektu and "Song of General Kim 
Il-song" sung loudly by the Korean people and the world people 
in praise of the great leader President Kim Il-song's 
revolutionary exploits. 
  Among them are stamps with kimilsongia and magnolia, the 
national flower, printed against the background of the old home 
in Mangyongdae, which reflect the best wishes of the Korean 
people and the world's revolutionary people. 
  There are also postcards and envelopes depicting in the 
immortal flower kimilsongia in full bloom the deep reverence of 
the Korean people and the world's revolutionary people longing 
for the old home in Mangyongdae. 

</TEXT>

