<H4>    Zambia, Zimbabwe Celebrations </H4>

<F P=102> SK0904103194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1016 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0904103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Celebration functions 
were held in different countries on the threshold of the 
birthday of the great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  A joint seminar took place in Harare, Zimbabwe. 
  In his report at the seminar N.T. Mawema, director of a 
department of the C.C. [Central Committee], the Zimbabwe African 
National Union-Patriotic Front and chairman of the Zimbabwean 
National Committee for the Study of the Chuche Idea, said: 
  President Kim Il-song is recognized worldwide as a genuine 
leader of the people. 
  History has registered many statesmen but such a great 
leader 
as President Kim Il-song cannot be found in it. 
  The chuche idea, the great guiding idea of the era of 
independence, has a strong attraction in leading the struggle of 
the world people to victory. This shows the exploits of the 
president as a rare thinker and theoretician. 
  Since President Kim Il-song successfully solved the problem 
of the succession of leadership for carrying forward the cause 
of socialism to accomplishment, the centre of the leadership of 
the cause of global independence and the cause of socialism has 
been established, firmly guaranteeing its victory. 
  A celebration meeting, a lecture meeting and an opening 
ceremony of a month of DPRK photo exhibition were held in 
Lusaka, Zambia, by the housing construction company of the Kim 
Il-song Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea and by the 
Coordinating Council of the Federation of Peace and Friendship 
Organizations of Mongolia. 

</TEXT>

