<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Receives Russian Folk Dance Troupe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Receives Russian Folk Dance Troupe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204110594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1045 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song today received former Soviet labour 
heroine and people's actress Zykina Lyudmila Georgievna, 
president of the Academy of Russian Folk Culture and head of a 
Russian folk song and dance troupe, participating in the 12th 
April Spring Friendship Art Festival, and her party. 
  Present on the occasion were Chang-Chol, vice-premier and 
minister of Culture and Art, and officials concerned. 
  The guests warmly congratulated President Kim Il-song on his 
birthday and wished him good health and long life. 
  After expressing thanks for this, President Kim Il-song had 
a 
talk with them in a cordial and friendly atmosphere and gave a 
luncheon for them. 
  He was presented with a gift by the head of the Russian folk 
song and dance troupe. 

</TEXT>

