<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Notes Kim Chong-il's Work on Health Care </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Notes Kim Chong-il's Work on Health Care </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0904110594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1031 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0904110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Guideline for Development of Chuche-Based Health Service" </F>
-- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
dedicates an article to the 20th anniversary of the publication 
of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il's famous work "On 
Further Developing Health Care for the People" (April 9, 1974). 
  The author of the article says: 
  The work is a highly important guideline which opened a 
bright road of developing health service to a new, higher stage 
as required by the modelling of the whole society on the chuche 
idea. 
  The work says socialist medicine is preventive medicine, the 
basic mission of which is to prevent diseases and protect and 
promote the health of the people. 
  On the basis of a scientific exposition of the essence, 
character and basic mission of socialist medicine, the work 
calls for correctly implementing the party's policy of 
preventive medicine through energetic hygiene propaganda, 
hygiene culture, prevention of pollution and anti-epidemic work. 
  The work gives answers to all questions arising in the 
development of health care, including the enhancement of the 
standard of medical (?assistance), development of chuche-based 
medical science and technique and improvement of the quality of 
medical education. 
  The work has served as a powerful weapon in exalting the 
health care system of Korean-style socialism centred on the 
masses because it gives answers to theoretical and practical 
questions in the improvement of socialist health service and 
helps further develop health service as required by our 
revolution and the reality of health care. 
  A phenomenal progress has been made in health service and 
its 
material and technical foundation has been consolidated through 
the efforts to implement the tasks set out in the work over the 
last 20 years. 
  Today the number of doctors in Korea is 29.7 per 10,000 
people and that of hospital beds is 136. This is the highest 
level in the world. 18.4 times of medical service is given to 
each head of the population in a year. Life expectancy at birth 
is 74.5 years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

