<H3> <TI>   German, Peruvian Parties Write to Kim Chong-il </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German, Peruvian Parties Write to Kim Chong-il </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1104070994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0556 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1104070994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il received a letter of solidarity from Werner 
Schulwese, chairman, and Hans Wauer, vice-chairman, of the 
Central Committee of the Communist Party of Germany, supporting 
the struggle of the Korean people to defend the dignity of the 
nation and the sovereignty of their country. 
  Expressing full support to the policies of the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea to cope with an armed intervention of 
imperialists, the letter said that the members of the Communist 
Party of Germany would stand firm on the side of the Korean 
people determined to defend socialism at a time when the 
imperialists are becoming undisguised in their campaign for 
pressure on Korea. 
  In a message to Comrade Kim Chong-il, Genaro Ledesma 
Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants 
and Students of Peru, expressed deep apprehensions for the grave 
danger of war created by the United States on the Korean 
peninsula recently after totally reversing the agreed 
conclusions reached between the DPRK and the USA in New York, 
and extended full support and solidarity to the Korean people in 
their struggle for the cause of socialism. 

</TEXT>

