<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee 
of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] arranged a reception Sunday 
evening for the delegation of the Socialist Party of Kazakhstan 
[SPK] headed by its Co-Chairman P.V. Svoik on a visit to Korea. 
  Kye Ung-tae, member of the Political Bureau and secretary of 
the WPK Central Committee, said in his address that leaders of 
Socialist Party of Kazakhstan visited Korea in April last year 
and again this time. We are thankful for your sincerity, 
considering it an expression of deep trust and solidarity of 
your party with the great leader of our party and people Comrade 
Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il and with 
our party and our cause of socialism, he noted. 
  He highly estimated the efforts of the SPK to achieve 
national reconciliation and unity, defending faith in socialism 
and build a society where all people live an equal life and 
sincerely wished it new greater success in the future work to 
build an independent and democratic society. Co-Chairman P.V. 
Svoik said in his address that the delegation of his party 
visited Korea for the second time, which means that his party is 
continuously developing friendly relations with the WPK. 
  He said it was happy to visit Korea at the significant time 
of greeting the spring holiday of April when Comrade Kim Il-song 
was born. The delegation of the Socialist Party of Kazakhstan 
arrived here Sunday. 

</TEXT>

