<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Duma Deputies View Korean Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Duma Deputies View Korean Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0804121094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1023 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- Deputies to the state 
Duma of the Russian federation expressed deep concern over the 
situation of the Korean peninsula which had been brought back to 
an acute phase. 
  A joint statement was released on April 4 by seven deputies 
including the Deputy Speaker of the state Duma, A. Vengerovsky, 
and the chairman of the committee for issues of social 
federations and regional organizations of the state Duma, V. 
Zorkaltsev, with regard to the grave situation currently created 
on the Korean peninsula. 
  The joint statement said: "We are surprised and angered at 
the fact that some quarters of the United States, seeking the 
establishment of a so-called `new world order', have raised a 
new unjustifiable condition to our traditional ally, the DPRK, 
and are increasing the tension again, threatening that they will 
resume the `Team Spirit' joint military exercises with South 
Korea and not come to the third-round of the DPRK-U.S. talks." 
  The joint statement called upon the DPRK and the U.S. to 
take 
all necessary steps to continue the talks for guaranteeing peace 
on the Korean peninsula. 

</TEXT>

