<H3> <TI>   New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Joint Message Sent </H4>

<F P=102> SK0804121394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1020 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0804121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The Central Peoples' 
Committee and the Administration Council of the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea Thursday sent a joint message of 
greetings to the International Chuche Idea Seminar on 
Independence, Peace and Friendship which opened in New Delhi in 
celebration of the 82nd birthday of the great leader President 
Kim Il-song. 
  The current seminar is of particular significance as it is 
open at a time of historical turn when the cold war ended and 
the desire of the popular masses for independence has grown 
stronger than ever before, the joint message says, and goes on: 
  The chuche idea is the most independent idea for defence of 
the independence of the country and its free development against 
all manner of domination and subjugation; it is a peaceloving 
and internationalist idea which opposes aggression and war and 
urges the peoples of all countries to love and cooperate with 
one another and achieve common prosperity. 
  As they have strictly applied the chuche idea to the 
building 
of a new society under the wise guidance of the great leader 
Comrade Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il, 
the Korean people have been able to build an independent 
socialism centred on the popular masses and firmly defend the 
sovereignty of the country and strengthen friendship and 
solidarity with the world progressive people in face of the 
imperialists' moves to stifle our country, which have been 
intensified as never before. 
  When the idea of independence, peace and friendship 
indicated 
by the chuche idea is upheld, the age-old desire of mankind to 
live a free and peaceful life in an independent world and 
achieve an eternal prosperity, uniting and cooperating with one 
another, will certainly be realized. 
  Although there still remain on the globe the old forces 
seeking domination and subjugation, aggression and war and the 
people's cause of independence is undergoing a grim test, it is 
temporary and no force on earth can arrest the onward movement 
of mankind on the track of independence. 
  The message expresses the belief that the seminar will make 
a 
great contribution to the accomplishment of the noble cause of 
mankind for realizing the idea of independence, peace and 
friendship and wishes the seminar success. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

