<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Large Attendance' Reported </H4>

<F P=102> SK1004092594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0856 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1004092594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- An International 
Chuche Idea Seminar on Independence, Peace and Friendship opened 
with a large attendance in New Delhi Friday [8 April] on the 
threshold of the birthday of the great leader President Kim 
Il-song. 
  It was attended by delegations and delegates from 20 
countries, delegates of international and regional chuche idea 
study organisations and political, public and academic figures 
of India, more than 500 in all. 
  A delegation of Korean social scientists and a delegation of 
Korean social scientists in Japan were also present. 
  Indian personages including former President Giani Zail 
Singh 
made congratulatory addresses at the seminar. 
  They highly praised His Excellency President Kim Il-song as 
the great leader who embarked upon the road of revolution in his 
early years and has performed immortal feats for the cause of 
independence of mankind and sincerely wished him a long life in 
good health for the accomplishment of this cause. 
  Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the Association Korean 
Social Scientists Association, conveyed a joint message of 
congratulations from the Central People's Committee and the 
Administration Council of the DPRK to the seminar. 
  Introduced at the seminar were congratulatory messages from 
Indian President Shankar Dayal Sharma, Prime Minister P.V. 
Narasimha Rao and high-placed officials of India, Cambodian King 
Norodom Sihanouk, the chairman of the International Disarmament 
Committee, the UNDP [United Nations Development Program], the 
UNESCO and other international organisations and chuche idea 
study organisations of different countries. 
  Prof. and Dr. T.B. Mukherjee, president of the Asian 
Regional 
Institute of the Chuche Idea and vice director general of the 
International Institute of the Chuche Idea, made a report titled 
"Chuche Idea Is a Scientific Doctrine Indicating the Road of 
Independence, Peace and Friendship." 
  The seminar continues. 

</TEXT>

