<H3> <TI>   New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    ARICI President Awarded Prize </H4>

<F P=102> SK1204014694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2243 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204014694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- "International Kim 
Il-song prize" was awarded to T.B. Mukherjee, president of the 
Asian Regional Institute of the Chuche Idea (ARICI) who is 
vice-director general of the International Institute of the 
Chuche Idea. 
  An awarding ceremony took place in New Delhi on April 9. 
  Congratulatory speeches were made at the ceremony by former 
Indian President Giani Zail Singh, the former general secretary 
of the Indian National Congress Party (I), Director General of 
the International Institute of the Chuche Idea Shuhachi Inoue, 
Secretary of the National Council of the Communist Party of 
India M. Farooqi and Secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea Hwang Chang-yop who was leading a 
delegation of Korean social scientists. 
  They said the awarding of the "International Kim Il-song 
Prize" to T.B. Mukherjee was a common honor and joy for all the 
members of the chuche idea study organizations and the 
progressive people who are following the chuche idea, the most 
excellent of the progressive ideas founded by mankind, and 
struggling for global independence. 
  T.B. Mukherjee in his speech said he, as a soldier of the 
great leader His Excellency President Kim Il-song and the dear 
leader His Excellency Kim Chong-il, would resolutely fight to 
the end with firm confidence in the cause of socialism, the 
cause of independence, under whatever circumstances. 

</TEXT>

