<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Seminar Adopts Declaration </H4>

<F P=102> SK1204103494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A declaration was 
adopted at the international chuche idea seminar on 
independence, peace and friendship held in New Delhi. 
  It says the seminar was a more significant and auspicious 
meeting as it was held on the occasion of the 82nd birthday of 
respected president Kim Il-song, the founder of the immortal 
chuche idea and guide of the popular masses' cause of 
independence. 
  "The seminar stressed in unison that though the onward 
movement of mankind is undergoing a test, it is temporary, and 
the present time is an era of a historic turn in which the 
people refuse the old world of domination and subjugation and 
they are advancing toward a new independent world," the 
declaration notes, and continues: 
  "Independence, peace and friendship are the basic idea which 
must be applied to the international relations for the building 
of a new world, independent and peaceful, in which the peoples 
of all countries around the world would develop and prosper 
alike, loving and cooperating with each other as the common 
masters of the world. 
  "The great chuche idea is the true outlook on the world in 
our era whereby mankind can realise its age-old desire to live 
and develop independently and creatively, loving and cooperating 
with each other in a free and peaceful world without domination 
and subjugation, aggression and war. 
  "We express full support and firm solidarity for the just 
efforts of the Korean people to reunify the country 
independently and peacefully, firmly defending the cause of 
socialism under the banner of the chuche idea. 
  "Today the entire Korean people are waging a resolute 
struggle to defend and develop socialism, singleheartedly united 
around dear Comrade Kim Chong-il, the outstanding leader of the 
Workers' Party and people of Korea and supreme commander of the 
Korean People's Army, thus powerfully demonstrating the 
advantages and invincible vitality of anthropocentric socialism, 
an embodiment of the chuche idea. 
  "It is a noble duty of the followers of the chuche idea and 
the progressive people the world over to actively defend the 
socialism of Korea from the attack and abuses of the 
imperialists and reactionaries. 
  "We strongly reject any attempt to stifle the socialism of 
Korea under the pretext of `nuclear issue', regarding it as an 
act going against the trend of the times toward independence 
and a challenge to the progressives. 
  "We must not be pessimistic but optimistic of the events of 
the last decade of the 20th century and greet the new century 
with firm readiness and determination to more vigorously push 
ahead with the onward movement of history toward independence. 
  "No force can turn back the powerful flow of our era toward 
the building of an independent, new world under the banner of 
the chuche idea and the cause of independence of the masses 
will certainly end in victory." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

