<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Delhi Hosts International Chuche Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Seminar Ends Session </H4>

<F P=102> SK1204045994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0426 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204045994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The international 
chuche idea seminar on independence, peace and friendship which 
had been held in New Delhi in celebration of the birthday of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song closed on Sunday. 
  At the closing ceremony "Kimilsongism, Banner of 
Independence, Peace, Progress and Prosperity", a book published 
in India on the occasion of the birthday of President Kim 
Il-song, was introduced to the participants and a congratulatory 
message of a congratulatory group of the Indian youth read out. 
  Letters to the great leader President Kim Il-song and the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il were adopted at the closing 
ceremony. 
  Then followed the adoption of a letter to the Indian 
president, Shankar Dayal Sharma, and a declaration of the 
seminar. 
  Shuhachi Inoue, director general of the International 
Institute of the Chuche Idea, who is the "International Kim 
Il-song Prize" winner, in his closing address stressed that the 
current seminar was a historical gathering that vividly proved 
the validity and invincible vitality of the chuche idea through 
the successful discussion of the theoretical and practical 
questions and ways in opposing the imperialist aggression and 
arbitrariness and building an independent, peaceful new world on 
the basis of the immortal chuche idea. 
  On the same day, a banquet was arranged in New Delhi in 
celebration of the birthday of President Kim Il-song. 

</TEXT>

