<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hwang Chang-yop, Social Scientists Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hwang Chang-yop, Social Scientists Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1204051794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0428 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1204051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- A delegation of Korean 
social scientists led by Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the C.C., 
Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and chairman of the Association of 
Korean Social Scientists, returned home on Monday after 
participating in the International Chuche Idea Seminar on 
Independence, Peace and Friendship held in India. 
  It was met at the airport by Kim Yang-kon, vice-director of 
a 
department of the WPK Central Committee. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

