<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference of Natural Science Researchers Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference of Natural Science Researchers Held </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1104070694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0538 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1104070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- A national meeting of 
activists in natural scientific research was held here over 
April 8-10. 
  The meeting reviewed the achievements and experiences gained 
in natural scientific research in the past and discussed the 
tasks and measures to effect a new turn in scientific research 
conducive to implementing the party's revolutionary economic 
strategy. 
  The meeting was attended by Kang Song-san, Politburo member 
of the C.C. [Central Committee], Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] 
and Premier of the Administration Council, Kim Chung-nin, 
secretary of the WPK Central Committee, and officials concerned. 
  The meeting pointed out that to thoroughly implement the 
agriculture-first policy it is necessary to deepen research work 
contributable to carrying on the rural technical revolution on a 
higher stage, accelerating the green revolution and developing 
new branches of agro-science and to promote the 
industrialization and modernization of agriculture. 
  It laid stress on gaining new success in the research work 
to 
successfully solve the scientific and technical matters arising 
in carrying out the light industry-first policy and to develop 
foreign trade. 
  The meeting called for solving the urgent scientific and 
technical bottlenecks, developing the electronics, mechanic 
engineering, heat engineering of new materials, biology and 
chemistry onto a higher stage, deepening the research on such 
new scientific and technical fields as super-pressure, 
ultracryogenics and laser and putting great efforts to 
developing basic sciences as mathematics and dynamics. 
  A letter of pledge to the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il 
was adopted at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

