<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spring Friendship Art Festival Opens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spring Friendship Art Festival Opens </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Participants Honored </H4>

<F P=102> SK1004082694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1004082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 10 (KCNA) -- The Organizing 
Committee of the 12th April Spring Friendship Art Festival 
hosted a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture Saturday for 
the participants in the festival. 
  Invited to the reception were the members of foreign art 
troupes and members of overseas Korean art troupes. 
  Present there were Chang Chol, vice-premier and minister of 
culture and art, who is chairman of the festival organizing 
committee, Kang Hyon-su, chief secretary of the Pyongyang 
Municipal Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman 
of the Pyongyang Municipal People's Committee, other officials 
concerned and artistes in the city. 
  A speech was made at the reception. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

